    "body": "In https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/148676 the format of the `arraydescr` struct get changed, which meant that our representation was outdated and crashed.\r\n\r\nIt isn't easy to adapt it perfectly for both (if users are manually using the `arraydescr` type anyway) but we can make our `array.array.__getbuffer__` function not crash by hiding some of the details in C code.",
    "closed_at": null,
